<li id="cite_note-178"><b><a href="#cite_ref-178" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://www.redemmas.org/section/About/emma/" class="external text" title="http://www.redemmas.org/section/About/emma/" rel="nofollow">"Red Emma's Bookstore Coffeehouse&#160;: About&#160;: Who is Red Emma?"</a>. <a href="/wiki/Red_Emma%27s_Bookstore_Coffeehouse" title="Red Emma's Bookstore Coffeehouse">Red Emma's Bookstore Coffeehouse</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.redemmas.org/section/About/emma/" class="external free" title="http://www.redemmas.org/section/About/emma/" rel="nofollow">http://www.redemmas.org/section/About/emma/</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2008-02-24</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Red+Emma%27s+Bookstore+Coffeehouse+%3A+About+%3A+Who+is+Red+Emma%3F&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BRed+Emma%27s+Bookstore+Coffeehouse%5D%5D&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.redemmas.org%2Fsection%2FAbout%2Femma%2F&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Emma_Goldman"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
